				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				What this all burns down to is pretty much a war of high lvls vs low lvls. obviously Verant roots for the low lvls for some reason which i can't imagine. The reason this makes no sense is because the high lvls are the ones that have been paying Verant's way for the longest. I hear the lowbies always saying &quot;well, you got tons of cash so why not go buy them from some person?&quot; Thats pretty stupid, I can remember back when I was low lvl and I thought the same way, I thought all high lvls had more money than they know what to do with too, it's not that way at all. Even as a lvl 55 I still have to scratch around to get any cash. I dont know where everyone thinks the high lvls get all their &quot;vast treasures&quot; from. But I can tell you that those treasures dont exist. I dont know if Verant doesnt realize that or what. Maybe simply because they can type in a couple words and *poof* they got 100k, i dont really know. Yes, the is Velious too, which in order to do anyting in you have to have an uber guild with about 6 groups. Then you might say &quot;well just lvl up a differant character..&quot; but should I really have to? Some people might think differantly but personally I dont like staring at my spell book again for 35 lvls. Also there are a lot of new, better RPGs coming out very soon, the high lvls are going to get tired of just the same old thing and want something new, thus a lot of the high lvls will leave EQ. I'm sure the newbies would rejoice at that but one day even the newbies will be 50+ and feel the same way. I'll be one of those people leaving EQ for a better RPG. I had a good time with EQ but it's just gotten boring, I was going to stay when I heard about Luclin but with this loot code it gives me no reason to waste my money buying the expantion. Anyway, that's just my 2 cp.<BR>
Farewell.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Senain<BR>
