really, what it seems like they'll be doing is something like putting the Runed Totem Staff in a newbie garden, not primal velium. <BR>
<BR>
if you HAVE to see what all is dropping, why not buy it from one of the lower levels? they need the cash, and you have more than enough to spare, no doubt. or, level up a Vah Shir and snag it yourself.<BR>
<BR>
again, if you're out of the level range, why do you need the equipment? hell, mobs rarely drop items that are useful for the level needed to kill 'em, so you'd probably wind up getting utter crap, anyway. head to a zone where you get exp in the expansion, and pick up utter crap AND exp there.<BR>
<BR>
no one's trying to screw you over. but when there's zones all over Kunark and Velious that you have to be 45 + to even think about starting quests to get the keys for... it's time to throw the newbies a bone, too. rat whiskers and deathfist scalps don't really work well, you know?
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
